canonical:
  title: 薦法兄圓慧國統疏
  author: 釋無畏
  language: lzh
  text: 眞身無礙徧入衆生心想中妙法難思頓超三乘敎行外感如形對應若像生宜憑諸佛大事之因緣用導先師故鄕之行李惟彼還源之國統實吾並世之門兄自童孩至于長成以慈愛勤于訓誨法恩重如山岳無以報之齋供略備涓埃庶幾薦也伏願現前三寶令我圓慧國統之靈六根淸淨三智圓明受用長者家珍自他兼利游泳四方刹海賢聖同流餘澤所霑群萌等潤
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 薦法兄圓慧國統疏
  author: 釋無畏
  language: lzh
  text: 眞身無礙。徧入衆生心想中。妙法難思。頓超三乘敎行外。感如形對。應若像生。宜憑諸佛大事之因緣。用導先師故鄕之行李。惟彼還源之國統。實吾並世之門兄。自童孩至于長成。以慈愛勤于訓誨。法恩重如山岳。無以報之。齋供略備涓埃。庶幾薦也。伏願現前三寶。令我圓慧國統之靈。六根淸淨。三智圓明。受用長者家珍。自他兼利。游泳四方。刹海賢聖同流。餘澤所霑。群萌等潤。
korean:
  title: 법형 원혜 국통을 천도하는 글
  author: 석무외
  language: kor
  text: 참된 몸은 걸림이 없어 중생의 심상(心想) 속에 두루 들고, 묘한 법은 생각하기 어려워 삼승(三乘)의 교행(敎行) 밖으로 뛰어나나니, 그 감응이야말로 형상을 바로 대하는 것 같나이다. 마땅히 부처님의 큰 인연에 의지하여 선사(先師)의 고향 행차에 인도해야 하리이다. 생각하건대, 저 근본에 돌아가는 국통은 실로 우리 세상을 같이한 문형(門兄)이니, 어릴 때부터 장성에 이르기까지 자애로써 교훈에 애쓰셨으므로, 그 은혜의 무거움이 산악(山岳) 같아 갚을 길이 없사오매, 이에 약간의 재공(齋供)을 베풀어 정성껏 천도(薦度)하려 하옵니다.원하건대, 현재 삼보(三寶)께서는 우리 원혜 국통의 영혼으로 하여금 육근(六根)이 청정하고 삼지(三智)가 원만하여서, 장자의 집 보배를 받아서 씀에는 자타(自他)가 함께 이롭고, 사방의 절 바다[刹海]에 헤엄침에는 성현과 같이 흐르며, 남은 은택의 적시는 곳에 뭇 싹이 고루 윤택하게 하옵소서.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1140_010_0180&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Memorial Offering for the Dharma Brother Wonhye, National Preceptor
  author: Seok Muoe
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The true body knows no obstruction, pervading the thoughts and hearts of all sentient beings. The marvelous Dharma transcends conception, leaping beyond the teachings of the three vehicles. Like form reflected in a mirror, response arises naturally—so should we rely upon the great compassion of all Buddhas to guide the spirit of our departed teacher homeward.

    Consider now: this National Preceptor who has returned to the source is truly my elder brother in this world. From childhood until manhood, with loving care he devoted himself to my instruction. His kindness weighs as heavy as mountains, and there is no way to repay it. Though my humble offerings are meager as drops of water, I present them sincerely to aid his passage.

    I humbly pray that the Three Jewels before us will grant that the spirit of our Wonhye, National Preceptor, may find:

    The six senses purified and the three wisdoms perfected, so that he may receive and enjoy the treasures of the celestial mansion, benefiting both self and others alike. May he swim freely through the seas of buddha-lands, flowing in unity with all saints and sages. And may the remaining grace he bestows fall upon all creatures, bringing equal nourishment to every growing thing.
  footnotes:
    - The 'three vehicles' (三乘) refers to the Buddhist classification of teachings leading to arhatship, pratyekabuddhahood, and bodhisattvahood.
    - The 'six senses' (六根) in Buddhism comprise the five physical senses plus the mind itself.
    - The 'three wisdoms' (三智) traditionally refer to wisdom of the past, present, and future, or alternatively, different types of enlightened understanding.
    - The 'treasures of the celestial mansion' alludes to the infinite spiritual riches available to those who achieve enlightenment.
